Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.00,0:00:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Аниме будущего
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.87,0:00:07.00,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}2-ое марта 2013 года{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.04,0:00:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Сегодня будут показаны 4 коротких анимационных фильма,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.91,0:00:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}созданные по инициативе Министерства Культуры\Nдля поддержки молодых аниматоров.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.28,0:00:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Один из фильмов привлек внимание многих фанатов -\Nэто Академия Маленьких Ведьм от студии TRIGGER.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.02,0:00:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Огромное количество людей пришло на примьеру.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.73,0:00:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Далее на сцене режиссер "Академии Маленьких Ведьм" от студии TRIGGER -\NYoh Yoshinari и актриса озвучивания Megumi Han (голос Akko).
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.03,0:00:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(793,1029)}Академия Маленьких Ведьм\Nрежиссер Yoh Yoshinari{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.80,0:00:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,830)}Режиссер фильма Yoh Yoshinari -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.96,0:00:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,830)}харизматичный аниматор, с фанатами по всему миру,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.24,0:00:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,830)}выбрал удачный момент\Nдля своего режиссерского дебюта.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.28,0:00:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Я верю,что имя Yoh Yoshinari\Nуже широко известно среди любителей аниме.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.19,0:01:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Удивительно, но за эти 23 минуты,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.46,0:01:06.53,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Диктор Nippon Broadcasting - Yoshida Hisanori
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.19,0:01:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,было показано около 17 000 кадров,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.53,0:01:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,в то время как большинство других студий сделали бы не более 3 000.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.10,0:01:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Просто они были оплачены вашими налогами,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.00,0:01:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,и было бы обидно их тратить впустую...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.84,0:01:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, result-wise it may seem like a waste,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.17,0:01:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but the desire not to let it go to waste,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.14,0:01:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that in itself got everyone to do better.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.61,0:01:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they weren't really amateurs,\Nthey were still inexperienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.52,0:01:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so their material wasn't all that usable at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to give them plenty of guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.40,0:01:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The famous Yoh Yoshinari, training newcomers?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.57,0:01:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Many in the animation industry reacted with surprise.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.37,0:01:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Из восьми аниматоров студии пятеро\Nявляются молодыми специалистами с небольшим опытом.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.71,0:02:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This was also their first time\Nworking on theatrical animation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.38,0:02:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And so, behind the scenes of Little{\i0} Witch\N{\i1}Academia, was yet another "academy".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.92,0:02:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.03,0:02:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.90,0:02:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can say is I feel bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.83,0:02:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Я благодарен.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.10,0:02:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I think I've got it right,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.44,0:02:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes back with lots of revision points.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.44,0:02:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I end up feeling like I'm no good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.75,0:02:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The five young animators spent\Na grueling half year together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.62,0:02:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year there's some idiot who just has to show off,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.82,0:02:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,At last I get to ride a broom at school!\Nand I'll give them demerits mercilessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.12,0:02:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been so long, I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.56,0:02:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How did they overcome the high standards\Nset by director Yoh Yoshinari?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.00,0:02:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Narrator - Hidaka Noriko
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.84,0:02:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Join me, as we look back on those days of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How the Magic Was Created\N- Little{\i0} Witch {\i1}Academia Work Log~{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.58,0:03:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tokyo, Ogikubo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.25,0:03:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}TRIGGER is a new animation studio, founded in 2011.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nearly all of its staff members are from GAINAX.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.23,0:03:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The studio was founded by popular animators,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}well-known for series such as Gurren Lagaan,\Nwith an eye towards the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.64,0:03:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the first day of documentary filming.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Director Yoshinari is making\Nfinal adjustments to the storyboards.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.72,0:03:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never drawn a storyboard\Nin just two weeks before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.96,0:03:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,, No,{\i0} I {\i1}mean it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:51.63,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}TRIGGER Co-founder{\i0} - {\i1}Hiroyuki Imaishi\N(Gurren Lagaan, Panty & Stocking with Garterbelt)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't remember it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.29,0:03:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When drawing directly on storyboard paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:03:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't reorder them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:04:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Like if I want to insert a cut somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,or remove one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.37,0:04:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like it could get rather\Ndifficult. That's a bit stressful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.94,0:04:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, when drawing in the boxes,\Nif you're only thinking about images,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.95,0:04:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the sequence of cuts, then\Nyou don't get the sense of the flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.69,0:04:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When drawing on storyboard paper, you're\Nfocused more on the flow of the page,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so you worry about getting careless with the drawings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.63,0:04:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that how you draw manga?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a lot like manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kinda tricky drawing inside the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.24,0:04:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Everybody has their own way of drawing storyboards.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.18,0:04:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Director Yoshinari works by first\Nrandomly doodling the images he has in mind,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and then putting them together like a puzzle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The one problem is when the papers start to pile up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.16,0:05:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I go about trimming it down...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At this time, Imaishi-san is also struggling\Nwith the storyboards for KILL{\i0} la {\i1}KILL.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't you have your own\Nstoryboarding to do, Mr. Imaishi?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.54,0:05:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I do, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.67,0:05:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been able to draw\Na storyboard in just two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.34,0:05:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get back to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.85,0:05:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That evening, the new animators visit\NStudio TRIGGER for the first time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.03,0:05:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These five young animators\Nare all originally from GAINAX.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.57,0:05:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this many?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.30,0:05:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're all guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.84,0:05:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Little Witch Team is having\Ntheir first face-to-face meeting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The aim of this nine-person animation team\Nis to screen in March of the coming year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Yoshinari, any words from the director?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.09,0:06:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The concept behind this project\Nis to train new animators.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.93,0:06:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So please remember that\Nyou guys have the "leading role".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.46,0:06:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do my best not to drag you all down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.00,0:06:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it'll be enough to\Nprovide a pleasant environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.44,0:06:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't even given you the storyboards yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.55,0:06:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be uploaded today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.62,0:06:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It can get like this at times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.62,0:06:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly believe you can accomplish this.\NGood to be working with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.26,0:06:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These five have the leading roles in our film.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.26,0:06:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let's take a look at their profiles.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.30,0:07:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(606,1042)}Yuuto Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,884)}Yuuto Kaneko, age 26
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,858)}He'll be in charge of the scene with the Minotaur\Nin the underground dungeon, 45 cuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.29,0:07:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,858)}Actually, the candidates got to pick which\Nscenes they would be assigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.29,0:07:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,858)}He chose this one because\Nmonsters and muscles are his specialty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.90,0:07:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1369,1046)}Shouta Sannomiya
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.00,0:07:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}Shouta Sannoimya, age 26.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}He has 57 cuts, from after Diana's group descends into\Nthe dungeon, until the scene in the trash dump
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.00,0:07:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}He chose this section with lots of props because he\Nenjoys coming up with ideas for hints and jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:08:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(478,1045)}Masaru Sakamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}Masaru Sakamoto, age 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.00,0:07:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}He's in charge of the entire opening|\N before the title sequence, 44 cuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.00,0:08:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}As the animation director for {\b1}Medaka Box{\b0},\N he has the most experience
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}This time, instead of his usual everyday scenes, he's\Nchallenging himself with a flashy fantasy action scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.29,0:08:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1364,1044)}Hisao Dendou
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.36,0:08:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}Hisao Dendou, age 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.86,0:08:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}He has the start of the treasure hunt and the crowd scene\Nwhen the dragon flies out of the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.01,0:08:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}He chose these simple scenes that require time & effort because\Nno one else would want to do them, he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.22,0:09:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(536,1045)}Shuuhei Handa
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.22,0:08:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}Shuuhei Handa, age 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.60,0:09:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}He'll be in charge of the battle scene between\NAkoo and the dragon, 44 cuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.00,0:09:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}He says, "I picked the coolest part!"\Ndemonstrating quite a simple personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.71,0:09:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The one who assembled this\Ngroup is the producer, Naoko Tsutsumi.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.99,0:09:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She was employed in production for Gurren Lagaan,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.22,0:09:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and has known the five since they were new\Ninbetweeners. Producer Naoko Tsutsumi{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.50,0:09:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In fact, she is Director Yoshinari's wife!\NProducer Naoko Tsutsumi{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.10,0:09:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In fact, she is Director Yoshinari's wife!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.97,0:09:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Since you already know Mr. Yoshinari's\Npace and how to talk to him,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.34,0:09:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there shouldn't be many problems on that front.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.84,0:09:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you could say I know him, but I still\Nthink it'll be highly demanding work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.42,0:09:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's so much material,\Nhow will everyone deal with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.85,0:09:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like we just have to take the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.80,0:10:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm looking forward to it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.26,0:10:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to work with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.97,0:10:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Three days later, on August 6th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.48,0:10:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Today is the "Anime Mirai" Project\Nexplanatory meeting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.61,0:10:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There are 60 attendees, representing four studios:\NTRIGGER, Madhouse, ZEXCS, and Gonzo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anime {\i1}Mirai{\i0}\NGood morning everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,(Good morning)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.66,0:10:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a quiet response.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.30,0:10:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I like these reserved voices.\NSince I'm an animator.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.70,0:10:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Kamimura, an animator\Nserving as Project Manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.80,0:10:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Kamimura, an animator\Nserving as Project Manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.80,0:10:47.14,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Project Manager - Nurturing\NKouko Kamimura
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.28,0:10:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}{\i1}The Ministry of Culture has entrusted "Anime Mirai" to an\Nindustry group named JAniCA.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.28,0:10:55.22,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\pos(586,1004)}Japan Animation Creators Association{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.22,0:10:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}{\i1}The Ministry of Culture has entrusted "Anime\NMirai" to an industry group named JAniCA.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.42,0:11:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The four studios chosen in the competition will\Nreceive grants of 38 million yen for each film.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.03,0:11:10.63,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\pos(733,1006)}TV series cost per episode: 10-20 million yen
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.63,0:11:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,940)}{\i1}Because studios tend to prioritize efficiency, the goal\Nis making sure that funds are used for nurturing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.90,0:11:12.07,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Project Manager - Administration\NAttorney Daisuke Okeda
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a few guidelines that must be complied with, at minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:16.91,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Project Manager - Administration\NAttorney Daisuke Okeda
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a few guidelines that must\Nbe complied with, at minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.41,0:11:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because those like myself must respond when\Nviolations of these guidelines come to our attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,these issues could ultimately result in contract\Ncancellation, so please take care to follow the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.05,0:11:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The rules established by Anime Mirai\Napply to many aspects of work.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.26,0:11:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,890)}{\i1}For example, animation staff must all work in\Nthe same location, to share time together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.50,0:11:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,890)}{\i1}They are forbidden to work from home.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.24,0:11:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,890)}{\i1}Corrections should not all\Nbe made by the lead animator.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.74,0:11:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,890)}{\i1}They should instead explain the issues and let\Nthe animators make the fixes themselves.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.38,0:12:06.00,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1608,2)}Unified Lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.51,0:12:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,890)}{\i1}The young animators must participate in a\Nseries of lectures and activities sponsored by Anime Mirai,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,890)}{\i1}in order to form relationswith other animators\Nand improve their skills and knowledge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:11.33,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1426,1)}Lectures on Copyright Law & Contracts
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.33,0:12:12.33,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1574,1)}Acting Workshops
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.33,0:12:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Creating an environment where young\Nkey animators can learn and grow is top priority.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.37,0:12:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Director Yoshinari is thoughtful after the meeting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.28,0:12:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}The grant money does come with strings attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.45,0:12:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}It's not for making the perfect film.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.22,0:12:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}Teaching the creation process\Nis what's important here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.23,0:12:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}If I try to put in 100% effort,\Nit'll just cause more trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.47,0:12:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,850)}I need to hold back a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.70,0:12:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd better save this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:13:03.68,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Representative Director\NMasahiko Otsuka
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.88,0:13:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Our creators always say the same thing at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.15,0:13:09.02,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Director Kazuya Masumoto\NBoth with {\i1}Panty &{\i0} Stocking and {\i1}Gurren{\i0} Lagaan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.02,0:13:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Director Kazuya Masumoto \NThey say, "I had trouble last time, so this time I'll do it well!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.75,0:13:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It never turns out that way.\NEveryone's keyed up at the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.06,0:13:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We all know now how things turned out in the end.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.70,0:13:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}August 30th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}About 2 weeks into animation drawing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.58,0:13:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The young animators at TRIGGER have\Nbeen wrestling with the layout stage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.62,0:13:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They use Director Yoshinari's storyboards and designs\Nas reference to produce a rough draft of each cut.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At this point, there are no complete cuts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:54.00,Default - overdub,,0,0,0,,{\pos(541,314)}Animator Count  Status of Cuts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:54.00,Default - Top Typsetting,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,421)}Handa\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NDendou\N\N\N\N\N\N\NKaneko\N\N\N\N\N\N\NSannomiya
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, there are no complete cuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.26,0:13:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At this point, there are no complete cuts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.80,0:13:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We {\i1}thought Director Yoshinari's\Nchecks might be too strict, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.57,0:14:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have my first cut checked today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.10,0:14:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is there a lot?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.61,0:14:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It took a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.65,0:14:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even after that, Mr. Handa\Nrechecks over and over again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.89,0:14:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was well into the evening when he\Nfinally felt ready to present his cut.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}You might have applied too much depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.72,0:14:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}Even if the captured screen is small...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}Wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.15,0:15:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}See, her hips go down in this part,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.19,0:15:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}but earlier she held this pose the whole\Ntime, even when bending forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.93,0:15:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,870)}so make the flow here more like this. Then when\Nshe's putting force into it, turn more to this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.17,0:15:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,870)}If you don't create flow, the sense\Nof force doesn't come through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.68,0:16:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,870)}Also, it'd be good if you\Nmodulated her pose changes more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.90,0:16:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,870)}Instead of moving in a straight line,\Ndo it more circular...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.01,0:16:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,870)}That way feels better?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.58,0:16:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The greatest corrections are for the movement\Nof her hip as she raises herself up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.05,0:16:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.75,0:16:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These are the two cuts in the second half of the story\Nwhere Akko grabs the sorcerer's stone and slides away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.13,0:16:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She stands up from a seated position, then\Ndashes while still partially bent over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.17,0:16:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She slides, grabs the sorcerer's stone,\Nthen gets up again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.34,0:16:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The shape of her back when\Nstanding is the point of this correction.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:17:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While running, her hips are low,\Nand her back is arched downward.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.95,0:17:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Her back rounds only at the moment when she\Nstands up, then returns to the previous posture.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.89,0:17:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}By doing so, instead of letting\Nenergy escape as she stands,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.83,0:17:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it gets transmitted through her back\Nto create a sense of driving force.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.47,0:17:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I hadn't really considered that\Nstuff about energy escaping before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.30,0:17:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.37,0:17:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.60,0:17:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole feel of the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is just better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.12,0:18:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The picture is just different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.04,0:18:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He keenly feels the difference in skill between\Nhimself and Director Yoshinari.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.52,0:18:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the first of many days of anguish.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}About two months into the\Nanimation drawing process,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.83,0:18:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}some of the backgrounds for the film are ready.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.37,0:19:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The background art supports the worldview\Nof Little Witch Academia.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.71,0:19:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How is it created?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.98,0:19:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We don't get to see this very often.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.18,0:19:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.52,0:19:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose a good 80% of\Nbackgrounds are now done digitally.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.26,0:19:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But this project will be using paint?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.93,0:19:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are using poster paints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.13,0:19:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ah, sounds familiar.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.20,0:19:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, poster paints and drawing paper.\NSame as from elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.08,0:19:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With them you create such magical art.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.29,0:19:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the background art\Nactually used in the main story.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.86,0:20:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The delicate brush strokes\Nare just like in a real painting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.80,0:20:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While appreciating the hand-drawing, we'd\Nalso like to capture the art in recording.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.67,0:20:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They set up a fixed camera above Mr. Kaneko's desk.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the camera, it looks just like a pro's desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.69,0:20:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Neat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.29,0:20:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, let's watch a day's work in fast-forward.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}First, after setting the overall tone with the undercoat,\Nhe adds depth with trees and shading.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.64,0:20:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He paints in the entire tower, until it looks\Nbalanced, then takes a short break.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.78,0:20:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After that he draws in all the details at once,\Nthen he dries the painting, and it's finished.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.47,0:21:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Amazing. It really looks incredible up close.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.44,0:21:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good job.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.51,0:21:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How long did it take altogether?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.45,0:21:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A full nine hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.02,0:21:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How many seconds was that cut again?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.19,0:21:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's on the long side for a background\Npan-down, maybe 4 or 5 seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.26,0:21:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's long?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.80,0:21:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It is, for a background-only cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.77,0:21:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For animators to do a 1-second cut,\Nit probably takes a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.68,0:21:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sorry, Art Director Kaneko...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.48,0:22:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The animation team has actually\Nbeen much less efficient than that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.15,0:22:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The blue tags are layouts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.36,0:22:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The yellow tags are completed key art.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.09,0:22:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}According to the schedule, half of these\Ncuts should be yellow by now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.63,0:22:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the youngsters have only\Ngotten the OK for one cut apiece.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.40,0:22:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Four of the five are having trouble\Nprogressing beyond the layout stage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.68,0:22:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One of them, Mr. Dendou, is getting feedback.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.72,0:22:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The corrections are for dialogue cuts\Nwhich have hardly any movement.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.79,0:22:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What could be wrong with them?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.06,0:22:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The answer lies in this diagram by Director Yoshinari.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.04,0:23:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.75,0:23:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What advice did you get?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.86,0:23:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The position and perspective\Nof the characters are a bit off.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Also the angle's not what the storyboard intended.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.04,0:23:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I originally had the camera above,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.41,0:23:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's actually better to use a lower angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.45,0:23:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And due to the positions, her eyes\Nshould look towards the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.55,0:23:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I had her looking towards the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see, it's more focused to the center this way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.09,0:23:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The target dragon is over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.10,0:24:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on these positions, the target\Nshould be here, but I have it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.50,0:24:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They're facing this way, with the camera\Nabove them, and it's incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.08,0:24:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The teacher is gazing up at the rampaging dragon,\Nwhile Akko and the other students are between them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.65,0:24:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To show the back and forth of multiple\Ncharacters talking to each other,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.29,0:24:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you need a firm grasp of the\Nrelationships between their positions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.50,0:24:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! Well, I leave it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.33,0:24:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The diagram that Director Yoshinari\Nmade was for this purpose.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.34,0:24:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It shows the positioning of\Nthe five characters and the four cameras.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.01,0:24:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Since cut 268 has the camera between the dragon and\Nthe teacher, the focus should be towards the right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.19,0:24:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The camera position in cut 263 is horizontal and\Nat a distance, so there's almost no angling.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.63,0:25:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Cut 269 has the camera partially inside the\Ngroup. The teacher is shown obliquely.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.10,0:25:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Only cut 271 has a mismatch. Can you spot it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.04,0:25:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You draw while visualizing\Nthis arrangement in your head.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.98,0:25:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is another fundamental skill for animators.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.45,0:25:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you agree with the advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.75,0:25:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I can't believe I didn't realize it sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.79,0:25:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be able to tell with more experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.03,0:25:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't really know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.67,0:25:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell without seeing them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.34,0:25:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I can do it eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.49,0:26:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}November 15th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.69,0:26:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the start of a lecture series\Nsponsored by Anime Mirai.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.63,0:26:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.77,0:26:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.77,0:26:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't do my work, I won't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.97,0:26:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to get it done.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.17,0:26:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He photocopied a layout sheet to work\Non during the few brief pauses.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.85,0:26:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mr. Sannomiya! You'd better\Nput that away once class starts!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.16,0:26:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The third course in the series is a photography\Nlecture, followed by camera training.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.43,0:26:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To learn how to compose scenes logically,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.80,0:26:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they're learning how to do real photography\Nwith a single-lens reflex camera.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.67,0:26:55.34,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Photographer\NKouji Suwa
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.34,0:26:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's master focus, exposure, composition,\Nand equipment, and included with that is the lens angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.38,0:27:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As these have had a great\Ninfluence on animation drawing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.18,0:27:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say they have many elements in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.86,0:27:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After the lecture comes photography practice.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.73,0:27:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Each of them carries a camera for\Na photography meet at a nearby shrine.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.91,0:27:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Although they seem to be looking at the same scene,\Neach person has their own way of framing it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.52,0:27:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mr. Handa, what are you photographing?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.88,0:27:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A botcho.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.55,0:27:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, "botcho" must be dialect.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.96,0:27:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.99,0:27:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That bit sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.39,0:27:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Bit?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.20,0:27:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You have a unique point of view.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.93,0:27:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.61,0:28:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Spending day after day stuck at their desks,\Nthey haven't been out in the sun like this in some time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.88,0:28:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a brief moment of freedom.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.55,0:28:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.06,0:28:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.59,0:28:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.46,0:28:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.46,0:28:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what're you guys up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.39,0:28:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just some effects practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.06,0:28:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.94,0:28:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're making a video?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.27,0:28:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Broken into shots I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.51,0:28:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.95,0:28:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I get it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.88,0:28:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Effects practice...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.96,0:28:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get the balance right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.20,0:28:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I want it to look good broken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.93,0:29:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is this really going to help?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.04,0:29:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Starting tomorrow, they'll be back at work in the studio.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.58,0:29:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}January 8th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.59,0:29:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After the new year, TRIGGER moved to \Na different floor of the same building.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.29,0:29:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're still in the middle of tidying up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.60,0:29:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Happy New Year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.66,0:29:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.57,0:29:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You've finally moved to the new ﬂoor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.14,0:29:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we didn't run into much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.24,0:29:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But it still feels a little unfinished in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.38,0:29:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So what is the boss up to?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.25,0:29:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm filling the humidifier right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.92,0:29:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How is the project going?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.39,0:29:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be done with the key frames,\Naccording to the schedule,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.26,0:29:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but it looks like we're a bit behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.73,0:30:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not too bad though. We should be able to finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.64,0:30:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Did you fall behind in the hassle of moving?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.81,0:30:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hmmm,{\i0} that might not be the only reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.62,0:30:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At this time the key animation\Nis about a third of the way complete.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.79,0:30:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Out of 400 cuts, 100 have\Nfinished animation with color added.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.46,0:30:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These are assembled into a test film. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.37,0:30:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The scenes with the youngsters\Nin charge have few cuts with color.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.01,0:31:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Most are unfinished,\Njust captures of the layout line drawings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.05,0:31:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Especially prominent are the cuts where the backgrounds\Nare complete, but the characters are pure white.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.70,0:31:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The only ones that provide\Npeace of mind are the Minotaur scenes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.37,0:31:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were done by Mr. Kaneko, who has\None year of key animation experience.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.01,0:31:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The rule is that Little Witch Team\Ncomes to work at 2 PM.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.15,0:31:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the nearly-deserted studio, we find Mr. Kaneko.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.32,0:31:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're here early.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.83,0:31:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hi, long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.53,0:31:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Long time no see.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.40,0:31:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'm here early?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.27,0:31:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I went home early yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.77,0:31:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What time?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.28,0:31:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,About 2 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.48,0:31:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's early?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.18,0:32:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The others keep working later.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.58,0:32:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're already in the final stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.32,0:32:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have a little left in my part,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.76,0:32:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but on the whole there's still a lot to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.56,0:32:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So you'll be taking over\Nsome of the others' cuts now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.53,0:32:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.67,0:32:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think you're up to it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.01,0:32:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.21,0:32:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}From the start, Mr. Kaneko\Nhas progressed at a good pace.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.19,0:32:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The part he's in charge of has only 2 cuts left.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.23,0:32:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mr. Kaneko's working pace has sped\Nup as the second half approaches.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.10,0:32:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He wants to finish his work as soon as possible\Nto help his friends with their difficult cuts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.37,0:33:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's especially worried about\NMr. Sakamoto, who sits next to him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.39,0:33:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How's progress?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.40,0:33:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Finished for now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.86,0:33:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.80,0:33:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm wondering what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.53,0:33:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I got my cut back with corrections.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.21,0:33:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My first draft was awful. It really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.12,0:33:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it to the end, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.06,0:33:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,These are layouts, showing the flow of movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.56,0:33:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The pink is the director's,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.67,0:34:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the white part is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.18,0:34:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So what's different?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.58,0:34:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The motion, the whole performance, is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.52,0:34:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I basically just went by the storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.49,0:34:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But doing it that way makes it a little less exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.66,0:34:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to improvise,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.67,0:34:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't really get the image in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.60,0:34:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I draw more like the storyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.74,0:34:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,while Mr. Yoshinari starts out like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.78,0:34:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so it makes sense that the\Nmovements turn out different.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.98,0:34:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah, I see.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.99,0:34:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let's compare and see just what's different.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.86,0:35:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The pink first half is Director Yoshinari's,\Nand the second half is Mr. Sakamoto's.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.13,0:35:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}While the director's part\Ndoes move more gracefully,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.77,0:35:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mr. Sakamoto's version\Nalso has plenty of charm.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.31,0:35:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It seems that animators can\Nspot differences the rest of us can't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.65,0:35:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I'm going to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.82,0:35:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Do you find yourself becoming more negative\Nas you work on the project?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.43,0:35:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pessimistic by nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I think I've got it right,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.74,0:35:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes back with lots of revision points.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.04,0:35:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I end up feeling like I'm no good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.52,0:36:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had much confidence to begin with...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.56,0:36:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But up close, I can feel that\NDirector Yoshinari is a true genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.36,0:36:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I spend hours working on a cut,\Nthen Mr. Yoshinari fixes it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.77,0:36:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it only takes him an hour or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.15,0:36:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me realize that I have a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.16,0:36:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.00,0:36:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The young animators all keep\Nsaying the word, "genius".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.47,0:36:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But what does the work of a genius look like?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.71,0:37:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here Director Yoshinari is busy correcting layouts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.95,0:37:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Like before, we set up a fixed\Ncamera to record him as he works.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.96,0:37:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's the secret behind\Nthe renowned "Yoshinari Animation"?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.07,0:37:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As we watch him work, we're surprised\Nat the lack of indecision in his lines.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.04,0:37:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He hardly uses the eraser.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.81,0:37:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He also flips through the drawings much\Nless often than the youngsters.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.22,0:37:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He progresses before our eyes, as if the drawing\Nwere already finished inside his head.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.88,0:38:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He seems to have found a problem.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.82,0:38:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's correcting the placement\Nof this sheet with Akko running.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.62,0:38:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He cuts off the top part with the holes,\Nslides it over, then reattaches it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.13,0:38:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's an old technique for working more efficiently.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.37,0:38:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These are 9 seconds of cuts that\NMr. Sannomiya agonized over for two days.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.68,0:38:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Marking up nearly all the\Ndrawings took him a mere 4 hours.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.12,0:38:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These are the final corrections\Nto Mr. Sannomiya's portion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.89,0:38:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In all, three cuts have been sent back to him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.31,0:39:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can say is I feel bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.25,0:39:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.22,0:39:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever someone revises my work,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.62,0:39:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I assume that they'll return\Nit completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.59,0:39:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Yoshinari incorporated my idea,\Ninstead of abandoning it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.10,0:39:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I personally find that very hard to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.67,0:39:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The part where Diana kicks off from\Nthe wall was not in the storyboard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.58,0:39:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was Mr. Sannomiya's original idea.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.72,0:39:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If we compare them, Director Yoshinari\Nhardly changes the base poses.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.49,0:39:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He just reordered the modulations for the act\Nof standing up from a crouching position.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.76,0:40:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to settle this!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.83,0:40:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,50, good day to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.53,0:40:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He took this bit, which I drew to go this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.47,0:40:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and went with it without turning it into\Nsomething completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.19,0:40:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He restrained the urge to just do it his way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.72,0:40:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead worked with my clunky movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.93,0:40:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's no small feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.43,0:40:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he did this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.57,0:40:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take in what he was trying to show me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.78,0:40:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's wonderful that\Nhe's teaching us in this manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.69,0:41:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you proud to be one of his disciples?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.52,0:41:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not worthy to be called a disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.92,0:41:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But yes, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.80,0:41:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad he's teaching me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.60,0:41:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Thank you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.90,0:41:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wordless communication through drawings,\Nbetween fellow animators.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.95,0:41:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One month until the deadline.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.28,0:41:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}January 10th. Today, we observe\Nanother part of the process:{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.86,0:41:45.33,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In-between Checker\NNahoko Kosugi{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.33,0:41:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Checking the in-between animation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.73,0:41:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She literally Inspects the completed\N animation drawings one by one,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.00,0:41:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}checking for any in between mistakes or omissions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.48,0:42:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She is searching for mistakes\Nin 17 thousand animation drawings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.12,0:42:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Patience and concentration are necessary skills.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.53,0:42:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is my first time seeing\Nan actual in between animation check.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.77,0:42:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you'll find it entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.67,0:42:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, it's quite interesting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.64,0:42:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm just going like this the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.58,0:42:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't tell what I'm doing, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.44,0:42:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.85,0:42:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it's just flip, flip, flip.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.82,0:42:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So it's like checking a flip book.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.85,0:42:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're checking if the claws move correctly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.62,0:42:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.42,0:43:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I flip back and forth so much is\Nbecause I keep changing the area I'm checking.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.64,0:43:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If it seems fine,\NI check the picture as a whole last.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.02,0:43:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What was the portion\Nyou were fixing with the pencil?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.32,0:43:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed this tooth had no shadow\Nwhen there should be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.54,0:43:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the tooth is gradually coming more into view,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.51,0:43:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm adding a little to each frame so the\Nshadow doesn't just appear suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.05,0:43:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This way it feels more natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.99,0:43:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The cut is from the endgame of the film, right\Nbefore Akko chants the magic spell.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.07,0:44:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The issue was the absence of shadows in the dragon's\Nmouth, at the moment it raises its neck.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.57,0:44:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The image on the right is from before Ms. Kosugi's check.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.11,0:44:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's certainly a pro to notice such a small detail!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.19,0:44:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even when the animation schedule is delayed,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.03,0:44:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the post-production work goes on,\Nto meet the final delivery date.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.97,0:44:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the day for editing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.27,0:44:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Usually only the director witnesses this part,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.78,0:44:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but this time all the young animators will be\Ncoming along for the sake of their education.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.81,0:44:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm planning on heading to editing soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.49,0:44:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You should come if you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.69,0:45:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.39,0:45:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's having a hard time getting them to budge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.93,0:45:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They want to focus on their animation drawings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.50,0:45:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you going?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.01,0:45:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going, Mr. Sakamoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.34,0:45:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to work a bit longer.\NRather, I won't finish in time if I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.88,0:45:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm past deadline, but I just feel like slacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.85,0:45:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Watching the editing is part of the job too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.72,0:45:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, I'll just end up slacking off.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.63,0:45:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Get involved in other aspects of the\Nwork besides animation drawing."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.67,0:45:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is one of the objectives for nurturing young\Nanimators that TRIGGER agreed to.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.34,0:46:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In a typical TV series, after submitting the key art, you\Nalmost never see your own work before it's broadcast.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.99,0:46:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These five are seeing this stage for the first time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.26,0:46:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Editing involves omitting or refining footage\Nto meet the predetermined film length.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.37,0:46:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}First they play it from the start,\Nto check impressions given by the whole.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.91,0:46:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Shining Arc!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.19,0:46:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That completes the preview.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.19,0:46:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That completes the preview.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.36,0:46:43.73,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Film Editor\NKentarou Tsubone (Real-T){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.73,0:46:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The editor, Tsubone, has an unreadable expression.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.46,0:46:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes to 24 minutes and 30 seconds.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.40,0:46:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's at the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.51,0:46:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any margin for removing more?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.95,0:47:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably cutting close as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.58,0:47:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.96,0:47:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So you have to make it shorter?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.03,0:47:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)}Yes, 25 minutes is the longest we can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.83,0:47:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)}Currently the film ends at 24 minutes 30 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.30,0:47:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)}but the ending credits would\Nhave to fit into 30 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.71,0:47:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)}So we need to make\Nthe feature closer to 24 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.81,0:47:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)}but there doesn't seem\Nto be a good place to make cuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.69,0:47:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,950)}The timing might change clue\Nto the characters' motions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.99,0:47:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,880)}The film needs to be complete before we\Ncan really start the editing process.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.96,0:47:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is there anything you're worried about\Nor anticipating in this process?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.97,0:47:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried about whether we'll finish on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.20,0:48:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the animation be ready on time?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.79,0:48:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At any rate, the drawings have to be completed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.50,0:48:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}January 13th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.77,0:48:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With the footage still unfinished,\Nit's rushed into post-recording.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.97,0:48:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All of the dialogue will be recorded on this day.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.18,0:48:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As with the editing, they're interrupting\Ntheir work to observe the recording.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.56,0:48:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hope they get a little something out of it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.40,0:48:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine, so please...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.80,0:49:07.07,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Voice of Akko\NMegumi Han
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.57,0:49:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,First there's a test run-through with the entire cast.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.21,0:49:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up! This is your first flight at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.48,0:49:22.42,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Voice of Flight Instructor\NMinami Takayama
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.42,0:49:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year there's some idiot who just has to show off,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.36,0:49:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll give them demerits mercilessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.73,0:49:27.89,Default - Background,,0,0,0,,At last I get to ride a broom at school!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.89,0:49:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been so long, I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.23,0:49:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And then it's time for me,\NNoriko Hidaka, to take my turn.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.47,0:49:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Today will be combat training.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.81,0:49:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This tower was built upon an ancient labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.45,0:49:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Your task is to descend into the labyrinth,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.75,0:49:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And retrieve one of the treasures hidden there.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.08,0:49:55.49,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Voice of Shiny Chariot\NNoriko Hidaka
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.29,0:49:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The team that finds the rarest treasure will receive the top score.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.96,0:49:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Your time limit is three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.76,0:50:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Make use of the magic you have been studying\Nhowever you like, and surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.33,0:50:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.33,0:50:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We take a break after this part.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.70,0:50:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Scriptwriter Otsuka and Director Yoshinari\Ndiscuss their visions of the characters.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.35,0:50:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we do more?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.15,0:50:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Watanabe Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.15,0:50:24.38,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Sound Director Jun Watanabe
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.38,0:50:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess a bit more of a lackadaisical teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.38,0:50:29.16,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Sound Director Jun Watanabe
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.16,0:50:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't take her job very seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.26,0:50:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She seems more gentle.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.73,0:50:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not very strict.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.50,0:50:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.04,0:50:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The cast gets direction from\Nthe Sound Director, Mr. Watanabe.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.18,0:50:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can we expand upon his directions,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.91,0:50:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to create voices that really suit our characters?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.05,0:51:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is where anime voice actors show their skills.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.46,0:51:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Go right ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.43,0:51:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, if you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.50,0:51:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.57,0:51:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Today will be combat training.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.57,0:51:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This tower was built upon an ancient labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.64,0:51:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Your task is to descend into the labyrinth,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.31,0:51:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and retrieve one of the treasures hidden there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.72,0:51:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The team that finds the rarest\Ntreasure will receive the top score.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.59,0:51:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Your time limit is three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.49,0:51:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Make use of the magic you have been studying\Nhowever you like, and surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.16,0:51:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.00,0:51:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.34,0:51:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That was great!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.84,0:51:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, really!\NThat was great!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.47,0:51:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that heart-pounding\Nexcitement you're feeling today?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.25,0:52:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that you young animators,\Nas you continue in your careers,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.78,0:52:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,can hold on to that feeling throughout it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.06,0:52:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Without getting hung up on concepts,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.13,0:52:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to find what suits you,\Nand take on new challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.36,0:52:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Though you may find yourselves\Ncriticized, or even rejected,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.47,0:52:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to develop, not in a small orderly\Nfashion, but in a big brash fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.32,0:52:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}January 14th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.18,0:52:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tokyo is having record-breaking snowfall.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.26,0:52:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The normally-aloof Mr. Handa\Nhas an earnest expression today.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.83,0:53:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He seems close to perfecting the fireworks key art\Nthat he's been wrestling with for a long time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.24,0:53:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In current anime, fireworks are\Nalmost always done with CG.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.32,0:53:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, Mr. Handa has animated the firework\Nstars by hand, down to the individual grains.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.20,0:53:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The story's last scene, symbolizing Akko's thoughts\Nin sparkling fashion, is the final highlight.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.41,0:53:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}His key art totals 38 sheets, including\Nmaterials for the special effects.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.42,0:53:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all by hand, so it took a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.96,0:53:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,About a week I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.90,0:53:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How long is the cut?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.86,0:54:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,4.5 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.50,0:54:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just for 1 bang.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.01,0:54:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope this work pays off.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.98,0:54:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the last one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.78,0:54:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.58,0:54:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I included many demands for the filming process.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.23,0:54:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll likely take them a while too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.33,0:54:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, is that it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.70,0:54:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.83,0:54:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Book for... "tataki".
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.17,0:54:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the rest is up to the in-between, painting,\Nand compositing departments.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.32,0:55:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The finished key art aims for a complete image.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.80,0:55:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is where the key animator's job ends.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.17,0:55:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good work, Mr. Handa.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.71,0:55:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the same building as TRIGGER we find\Nthe CG production studio "Sanjigen".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.68,0:55:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All film processing for\NLittle Witch Academia is performed here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.08,0:55:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Director of Compositing,\Nis a veteran known for his work on Gurren Lagaan.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.55,0:55:30.72,Default - Top,,0,0,0,,Compositing Director\NToyonori Yamada (Sanjigen)
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.92,0:55:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Compositing is the last step\Nin the production of an animated work.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.80,0:55:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Based on directions from the animators, they\Nadd special effects with the computer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.37,0:55:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They may use computers as a tool here, but the\Nconcepts behind the process are unexpectedly analog.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.55,0:56:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For instance, "tataki" is a technique passed\Ndown from the days of cell animation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.26,0:56:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The tataki materials created on paper are captured by\Nthe computer, then arranged for easier digital handling.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.57,0:56:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}First, a sequence of 4 sheets,\Nmatched up with Mr. Honda's layout.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.64,0:56:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell that it's moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.31,0:56:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.95,0:56:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are the light blue dots the "Tataki" effect?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.28,0:56:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, those small dots.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.52,0:56:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It definitely adds more pizazz to the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.73,0:56:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.66,0:56:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Adding these effects to the orange explosion\Nmakes it look more realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.34,0:57:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew, how many more pages do I have to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.01,0:57:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot more for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.02,0:57:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The large fireworks animation has 46 in-betweens.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.13,0:57:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When combined with this smooth movement,\Nthe four tataki frames are clearly not enough.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.20,0:57:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll have to add those\Neffects to the whole cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.41,0:57:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like 20 pages to go. Mr. Handa!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.39,0:57:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of works end up being\Nmore rough due to lack of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.96,0:57:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But I definitely feel the passion in this cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.97,0:58:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me want to do my best as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.81,0:58:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He definitely took a risk taking\Nso long to finish this cut by hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.66,0:58:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think I'll do what I can for him on this end.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.73,0:58:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can he finish this scene without destroying the\Nhand-drawn feel Mr. Handa put so much heart into?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.51,0:58:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mr. Yamada's trial and error continues.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.93,0:58:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the final push.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.26,0:59:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even late at night, they're still hard at work.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.17,0:59:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Though furnished with emergency nap areas,\Nthere's hardly any time to use them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.55,0:59:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They spend days and nights here working.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.29,0:59:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They only return home when they feel\Nthey absolutely must take a shower.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.26,0:59:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fatigue has reached its peak, and they\Ncannot progress as well as they'd like.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.04,0:59:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's a large amount of\Nwastepaper at Mr. Sakamoto's feet.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.44,0:59:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It seems that no matter how he tries, he can't\Nget Chariot's light illusions to look right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.44,1:00:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.54,1:00:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.78,1:00:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want anyone looking through that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.52,1:00:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just trash.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.45,1:00:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.82,1:00:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.99,1:01:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And then...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.66,1:01:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All the key animation is done.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.33,1:01:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The half-year spent on this film will soon be coming to an end.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.94,1:01:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.41,1:01:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}February 14th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.05,1:01:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite the luggage.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.02,1:01:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Director Yoshinari and the two producers have returned\Nto Japan after finishing the sound work in France.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.16,1:01:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's just barely before the deadline.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.46,1:01:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They go straight from Narita Airport\Nto the editing studio.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.10,1:01:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This small hard disk holds the completed film.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.04,1:01:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Everything up to now is included in there.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.91,1:02:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the last part of the job for these five.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.29,1:02:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we'll play it all the way through.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.03,1:02:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.51,1:03:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.81,1:03:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're setting off for the Land of Magic!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.61,1:03:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here's my last question for you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.91,1:03:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Do you like these young animators?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.35,1:03:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, hm.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.16,1:03:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to spend a little\Nmore time with them to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.50,1:04:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, we mainly\Ncommunicated through drawings.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.81,1:04:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If possible, I'd like them to\Ncontinue in this line of work.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.65,1:04:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many who leave the industry\Neven when they have potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.30,1:04:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I do hope I can work with them in the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.64,1:04:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Thank you very much.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.69,1:05:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Never forget that faith in yourself is magic!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.57,1:05:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How the Magic Was Created\N- Little{\i0} Witch {\i1}Academia Work Log~{\i0}
